headline: Paving the Way: Insights from Recent Driver's Education Study Uncovers Key Opportunities for Parents and New Drivers
summary: As part of its commitment to driving progress on the road, Progressive Insurance® surveyed 513 new drivers aged 18 to 25 who got their license in the last five years to understand what was most effective in preparing them for the road. The results suggest that the key to building driver confidence and competency is supervised practice time. headline: Progressive (PGR) Delivers 32.5% Earnings Growth, Challenging Cautious Profitability Narratives
summary: Progressive (PGR) posted standout numbers this year, with earnings growing 32.5% over the past twelve months, well ahead of its five-year average of 22.2% per year. Net profit margin improved to 12.6%, up from 11.2% last year, while its Price-to-Earnings ratio sits at 12.4x, which is below the US insurance industry average but above its peer group.
